body:
With SOGo I am allowed to enter an URL without trailing slash (/). From server to Android everything works fine. In SyncAdapter.java, checkDirtyAndroidEvents() the url is formed to send updates to SOGo:

``` java
SyncID = caldavCalendarUri.getPath() + newGUID + ".ics";
```

This one then results in a non-existing calendar as newGUID is appended to the URL without a slash to separate them.

Workaround: ensure you register the URL with a trailing slash.

Fix: We could add something like:

``` java
if(mURL.endsWith("/")) {
  SyncID = caldavCalendarUri.getPath() + newGUID + ".ics";
}
else {
  SyncID = caldavCalendarUri.getPath() + "/" + newGUID + ".ics";
}
```

I have three events on next Monday which do not get synced to my phone, although a similar event I created simultaneously for Wednesday is displayed. I created those events some weeks ago, but did not notice that they are missing until now.
What can be the cause for this? Deactivating a calendar and re-activating it did not help.

//edit: Those events are in the same calendar.
